The paper deals with the use of LASSO for recovery of structured high-dimensional signals, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus is on the choice of the governing parameter, which is a numerical optimization problem, and the paper provides analysis and simulations to aid in this choice, which falls under numerical analysis (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper also deals with stability analysis of the LASSO program, which is a topic in dynamical systems (cs.DS).
